# mcp_servers/ — MCP adapter layer

MCP servers expose this project's capabilities to MCP hosts (Claude Code,
Claude Desktop, any MCP client). Design rule: **no business logic here** —
each tool is a thin client of a REST endpoint owned by a real service, so the
service stays the single tested, secured surface and MCP protocol churn is
isolated in this adapter.

## {{ mcp_server_slug }}/

{% if mcp_server_language == "typescript" -%}
TypeScript server on the official MCP SDK (`npm install`, then run per its
`package.json` scripts).
{%- else -%}
Python FastMCP server (`uv sync`, then `uv run python -m src.server` for
STDIO mode).
{%- endif %}

Ships one example tool, `search_articles`, which calls the retrieval backend's
`POST /api/v1/retrieval` (retrieval only, no answer synthesis).
{% if include_rag_agent -%}
The backend is this project's `rag_agent` (`make rag-up`); `RAG_AGENT_URL`
overrides the default `http://localhost:8011`.
{%- else -%}
`include_rag_agent=false`: point `RAG_AGENT_URL` (default
`http://localhost:8011`) at your own service's compatible
`/api/v1/retrieval` endpoint.
{%- endif %}

Extend with `/mcp-builder` (see `.claude/skills/mcp-builder/`), keeping the
tool-wraps-REST rule.
